  <fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>This is an immediate consequence of <fr:link href="jms-00JG.xml" title="Paths and iteration" addr="jms-00JG" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00JG" /></fr:link>: by <fr:link href="jms-00JH.xml" title="The reflexive-transitive closure of an endo-relation" addr="jms-00JH" type="local">Definition <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00JH" /></fr:link> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\mathrel {R^{\circ *}}t]]></fr:tex> if and only if there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\mathrel {R^{\circ  n}}t]]></fr:tex>, which by <fr:link href="jms-00JG.xml" title="Paths and iteration" addr="jms-00JG" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00JG" /></fr:link> holds if and only if there existss a path from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[t]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> of some length <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
