            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00JH</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00JH.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="The reflexive-transitive closure of an endo-relation">The reflexive-transitive closure of an <fr:link href="jms-00JF.xml" title="Path in a directed graph" addr="jms-00JF" type="local">endo-relation</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>For <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\in \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, we define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *}\in \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to be the <fr:em>smallest relation closed under all finite <fr:link href="jms-00JF.xml" title="Path in a directed graph" addr="jms-00JF" type="local">paths</fr:link> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex></fr:em>, i.e. the <fr:em><fr:strong>reflexive-transitive closure</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 R^{\circ *} = \bigcup _{n\in \mathbb {N}} R^{\circ  n}
]]></fr:tex>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
